==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inhibitory
<hw>In*hib"i*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>inhibitorius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inhibitoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of
or pertaining to, or producing, inhibition; consisting in inhibition;
tending or serving to inhibit; <as>as, the <ex>inhibitory</ex> action of
the pneumogastric on the respiratory center</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would not have you consider these criticisms as
<qex>inhibitory</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lamb.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Inhibitory nerves</b></col> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>,
<cd>those nerves which modify, inhibit, or suppress a motor or secretory
act already in progress.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhibitory-motor</ent>⟦br⟧
